.TH "elfcorehdr_read" 9 "elfcorehdr_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
elfcorehdr_read \- read from ELF core header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" elfcorehdr_read
.BI "(char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "u64 *ppos "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
buffer where the data is placed
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes to read
.IP "ppos" 12
address in the memory
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function reads \fIcount\fP bytes from elf core header which exists
on crash dump kernel's memory.
